	(text_box "Separate ground planes?\nLCSC BOM - add screws 2mm?, nuts\nCheck LCSC quantities\nCheck LCSC + JLC order together\nBuy RP2040s\nDouble check RP2040 cutout\nGo PCBA to confirm chip placement\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 289.56 55.88 0)
		(size 76.2 16.2161)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "d3fd0b89-81fa-4ff1-b1d8-39231b043c46")
	)
	(text_box "# Networking: 2 modes\n\nStar (Installation mode): In this configuration, no USB cables are used. You have a heavy-duty central 5V power supply inside a distributor box. The box has a permanent $1\\text{ k}\\Omega$ resistor across its central data knot. 40-meter total radiating lines run out to each node using standard Ethernet cables.\n\nDaisy-Chain (Desktop mode): Use 2-wire cables (Data/GND only; 5V is disconnected to prevent backfeeding). Each node powers itself via USB. Plug a \"Terminator Plug\" (a loose RJ45 with a 4.7kΩ resistor between Pin 4 and GND) into any open jack at the end of the chain."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 213.36 -20.8638 0)
		(size 88.9 28.4838)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "d4f59ca7-67f0-43b5-bdc4-dcfddecd9640")
	)
	(text_box "1. CONTINUOUS LAYER 2 GROUND\n   Keep the entire Layer 2 as a solid sheet of copper. Do not split it. Return \n   currents will naturally stay separated if you follow spatial zoning on Layer 1.\n\n2. SPATIAL ISOLATION (ZONING)\n   Keep all digital components/traces on the left. Keep all analog components/\n   traces on the right. Never mix them.\n\n3. CLASS-D AMPLIFIER ISOLATION\n   The SPK_GND line must not dump noise into the quiet analog area. Run a thick, \n   independent trace from the SPK_GND pin straight to the system power input.\n\n4. TRACE CROSSINGS\n   If a digital trace must cross an analog trace, ensure they cross at a \n   perpendicular 90-degree angle to minimize capacitive crosstalk. Never run \n   them parallel to each other.\n\n5. CAPACITOR PLACEMENT\n   Route power through the decoupling capacitor pad *before* it hits the IC \n   power pin. Place the ground via immediately next to the capacitor pad."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 289.56 10.16 0)
		(size 88.9 43.4811)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "e0ae7316-e90b-4240-b7c0-524d480b3851")
	)
